# Manual example (switch.md:86): one input distributed to two outputs, ADDRESSED
# by a CV at `offset` (integer). offset 0 -> input on output1; offset 1 (10 V) ->
# input on output2. N = max(1,2) = 2, so inputs 2 reads 0 V.
patch <<<
[switch]
    input   = I1
    output1 = O1
    output2 = O2
    offset  = I7
>>>
@0 set I1 0.5
@0 set I7 0
@0 expect O1 0.5
@0 expect O2 0
@1 set I7 1
@1 expect O1 0
@1 expect O2 0.5
